{"analytics_identifier":null,"base_path":"/government/organisations/committee-on-radioactive-waste-management/about","content_id":"5f5a5b36-7631-11e4-a3cb-005056011aef","description":"The Committee on Radioactive Waste Management (CoRWM) provides independent scrutiny and transparent advice to the UK governments on the long-term management of radioactive waste.","details":{"attachments":[{"accessible":true,"alternative_format_contact_email":"corwm@energysecurity.gov.uk","assets":[{"asset_manager_id":"60992c61d3bf7f2883267b6c","filename":"Transcript_CoRWM_film_Mar_2021.pdf"}],"attachment_type":"file","content_type":"application/pdf","file_size":180049,"filename":"Transcript_CoRWM_film_Mar_2021.pdf","id":"8951452","number_of_pages":2,"title":"CoRWM: Geological disposal - transcript of film","url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/60992c61d3bf7f2883267b6c/Transcript_CoRWM_film_Mar_2021.pdf"}],"body":"<div class=\"govspeak\"><p><abbr title=\"Committee on Radioactive Waste Management\">CoRWM</abbr> is an expert committee sponsored by:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/department-for-energy-security-and-net-zero\">Department for Energy Security and Net Zero (<abbr title=\"Department for Energy Security and Net Zero\">DESNZ</abbr>)</a></li>\n  <li><a rel=\"external\" href=\"https://www.gov.scot/\">Scottish Government</a></li>\n  <li><a rel=\"external\" href=\"https://www.gov.wales/\">Welsh Government</a></li>\n  <li>\n<a rel=\"external\" href=\"https://www.daera-ni.gov.uk/\">Department of Agriculture, Environment and Rural Affairs (DAERA)</a> - Northern Ireland</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2 id=\"who-we-are\">Who we are</h2>\n\n<p><abbr title=\"Committee on Radioactive Waste Management\">CoRWM</abbr> has 12 members, who are experts in different aspects of radioactive waste management.</p>\n\n<p>Appointments are made on merit and political activity plays no part in the selection process. Any appointees’ political activity must be made public. None of the appointed members have declared any political activity. The Committee comply with the <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/committee-on-radioactive-waste-management-framework-document\"><abbr title=\"Committee on Radioactive Waste Management\">CoRWM</abbr> Framework Document</a>, published in 2020, which sets out the broad framework in which <abbr title=\"Committee on Radioactive Waste Management\">CoRWM</abbr> operates.</p>\n\n<h2 id=\"members\">Members</h2>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>\n<a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/people/nigel-thrift\">Sir Nigel Thrift</a>, Chair</li>\n  <li>\n<a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/people/penny-harvey\">Professor Penny Harvey</a> Co-Deputy Chair</li>\n  <li>\n<a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/people/derek-lacey\">Dr Derek Lacey</a> Co-Deputy Chair</li>\n  <li><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/people/mark-kirkbridg\">Mark Kirkbride</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/people/stephen-tromans\">Stephen Tromans KC</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/people/ray-kemp\">Dr Ray Kemp</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/people/claire-corkhill\">Professor Claire Corkhill</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/people/clare-bond\">Prof Clare Bond</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/people/simon-webb\">Simon Webb, CBE, FICE</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/people/malcolm-joyce\">Professor Malcolm Joyce</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/people/barry-lennox\">Professor Barry Lennox</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/people/peter-bryant\">Prof Peter Bryant</a></li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2 id=\"scope-of-our-work\">Scope of our work</h2>\n\n<p>The purpose of the Committee is to:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>give independent advice, based upon its remit and utilising the skills and expertise of its members</li>\n  <li>provide informed scrutiny of the available evidence to UK government and devolved administration ministers on the management of radioactive waste, arising from civil and, where relevant, defence nuclear programmes, including storage and disposal</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2 id=\"corwms-objectives\">\n<abbr title=\"Committee on Radioactive Waste Management\">CoRWM</abbr>’s objectives</h2>\n\n<p><abbr title=\"Committee on Radioactive Waste Management\">CoRWM</abbr>’s objectives are to provide independent evidence-based advice:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>to ministers of the UK government and devolved administrations, <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/nuclear-decommissioning-authority\">Nuclear Decommissioning Authority (<abbr title=\"Nuclear Decommissioning Authority\">NDA</abbr>)</a> and <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/nuclear-waste-services\">Nuclear Waste Services (<abbr title=\"Nuclear Waste Services\">NWS</abbr>)</a> on proposals, plans and programmes to deliver geological disposal, together with robust interim storage, for the UK’s higher activity radioactive waste</li>\n  <li>on other radioactive waste management issues as requested by sponsor ministers, including advice requested by the Scottish Government in relation to its policy for the management of radioactive wastes</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>In fulfilling its remit to provide independent and evidence-based advice, <abbr title=\"Committee on Radioactive Waste Management\">CoRWM</abbr> is expected to maintain an independent overview of issues relevant to the delivery of UK government and devolved administrations’ radioactive waste management programmes. It should bring to the attention of sponsor ministers issues that it considers to be:</p>\n\n<p>a) positive and worthy of note, or<br>\nb) concerns that, in the Committee’s opinion, need to be addressed.</p>\n\n<h3 id=\"corwm-video\">\n<abbr title=\"Committee on Radioactive Waste Management\">CoRWM</abbr> video</h3>\n\n<p><abbr title=\"Committee on Radioactive Waste Management\">CoRWM</abbr> has produced a short video about engaging with communities on geological disposal:</p>\n\n<p><a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=FQ0OnG2axrU\">The Committee on Radioactive Waste Management (<abbr title=\"Committee on Radioactive Waste Management\">CoRWM</abbr>)</a></p>\n\n<p>A transcript is available:</p>\n\n<p><span class=\"gem-c-attachment-link\">\n  <a class=\"govuk-link\" href=\"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/60992c61d3bf7f2883267b6c/Transcript_CoRWM_film_Mar_2021.pdf\">CoRWM: Geological disposal - transcript of film</a>  (<span class=\"gem-c-attachment-link__attribute\"><abbr title=\"Portable Document Format\" class=\"gem-c-attachment-link__abbr\">PDF</abbr></span>, <span class=\"gem-c-attachment-link__attribute\">176 KB</span>, <span class=\"gem-c-attachment-link__attribute\">2 pages</span>)</span></p>\n\n</div>","change_history":[{"note":"Updates made to the membership list.","public_timestamp":"2025-11-12T11:05:53Z"},{"note":"Removed Catherine MacKenzie from membership.","public_timestamp":"2025-08-06T12:22:59Z"},{"note":"Updated Radioactive Waste Management (RWM) to Nuclear Waste Services (NWS).","public_timestamp":"2024-01-16T10:54:56Z"},{"note":"Added new Member, Barry Lennox.","public_timestamp":"2023-08-23T14:22:48Z"},{"note":"CoRWM membership updated: added Malcolm Joyce","public_timestamp":"2023-08-01T13:14:31Z"},{"note":"Simon Webb added to list of Committee members.","public_timestamp":"2022-01-24T19:45:23Z"},{"note":"Dr Catherine MacKenzie and Clare Bond have taken up positions as Members of CoRWM as of 10 January 2022.","public_timestamp":"2022-01-10T12:39:20Z"},{"note":"Andrew Walters’ appointment ended on 1 September 2021.","public_timestamp":"2021-09-16T16:35:36Z"},{"note":"Professor Penny Harvey and Derek Lacey appointed as co-deputy Chairs.","public_timestamp":"2021-03-03T12:48:48Z"},{"note":"Objectives updated. ","public_timestamp":"2020-12-15T14:51:47Z"},{"note":"Updates on Work Programme","public_timestamp":"2015-11-09T15:34:17Z"},{"note":"First published.","public_timestamp":"2013-11-01T14:55:44Z"}],"corporate_information_groups":[{"contents":["5f55df59-7631-11e4-a3cb-005056011aef"],"name":"Access our information"},{"contents":["b956634b-2350-4cf5-b4de-3a6752f8abcf",{"title":"Jobs","url":"https://apply-for-public-appointment.service.gov.uk/roles?titleSearch=&body=1060"}],"name":"Jobs and contracts"}],"headers":[{"id":"who-we-are","level":2,"text":"Who we are"},{"id":"members","level":2,"text":"Members"},{"id":"scope-of-our-work","level":2,"text":"Scope of our work"},{"headers":[{"id":"corwm-video","level":3,"text":"CoRWM video"}],"id":"corwms-objectives","level":2,"text":"CoRWM’s objectives"}],"organisation":"5a99eabd-85c8-401a-9179-f2c11a928e98","tags":{"browse_pages":[]}},"document_type":"about","first_published_at":"2013-11-01T14:55:44+00:00","links":{"available_translations":[{"api_path":"/api/content/government/organisations/committee-on-radioactive-waste-management/about","api_url":"https://www.gov.uk/api/content/government/organisations/committee-on-radioactive-waste-management/about","base_path":"/government/organisations/committee-on-radioactive-waste-management/about","content_id":"5f5a5b36-7631-11e4-a3cb-005056011aef","document_type":"about","links":{},"locale":"en","public_updated_at":"2025-11-12T11:05:53Z","schema_name":"corporate_information_page","title":"About us","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/committee-on-radioactive-waste-management/about","withdrawn":false}],"corporate_information_pages":[{"api_path":"/api/content/government/organisations/committee-on-radioactive-waste-management/about/recruitment","api_url":"https://www.gov.uk/api/content/government/organisations/committee-on-radioactive-waste-management/about/recruitment","base_path":"/government/organisations/committee-on-radioactive-waste-management/about/recruitment","content_id":"b956634b-2350-4cf5-b4de-3a6752f8abcf","document_type":"recruitment","links":{}